<TITLE> DCCI seeks Tk 100bn for power, energy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)The Dhaka Chamber of Commerce and Industries has demanded that proposed budget allocation for the power and energy sector be raised to Tk 100 billion from Tk 61.15 billion to prop up the flagging sector. In a post-budget discussion in the capital on Friday, the business body generally hailed the budget for FY 2010-11 but expressed concern over some issues. Regarding various development projects, they demanded speedy implementation, improvement in the traffic and transportation system of the Dhaka City and prioritising Dhaka-Chittagong Economic Corridor. On tax and duty, they proposed withdrawal of all duty and taxes from telecom equipment, raising individual tax limit to Tk 2 lakhs, reduction of turnover tax rate and reverting VAT revision for SMEs. They criticised the government's decision to stop privatising the state-owned enterprises and demanded a reversal. The DCCI leaders welcomed the decision to withdraw VAT and reduction of duty on some raw materials. Finance minister AMA Muhith declared budget of almost Tk 1321 billion on Thursday for the coming financial year beginning on July
